23/05/2005
BERLIN, Germany -- EU security chief Javier Solana reiterated his belief that Bulgaria and Romania will enter the EU in 2007, in an interview with the German publication Bild am Sonntag on Saturday (21 May). 
Solana said that the two countries have achieved considerable progress in the field of reforms and that the EU's further enlargement is a logical step. 
(Rompres - 22/05/05; Reuters - 21/05/05)
